Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

== Guacamole ==

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Squeeze half the lime juice and a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} into a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Chop the @baby plum tomatoes{125}(cut into 2cm pieces) and pop into a #bowl{}. Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone, turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the flesh onto a #board{}. Chop half the avocado into 2cm chunks and pop into the bowl with the tomato. Set aside.

Roughly chop the remaining avo and put in another bowl, add the remaining lime juice. Season with salt and pepper, then roughly mash with a #potato masher{} (this is for your burger later).

== Chipotle Mayo ==

Halve the @burger buns{2}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Put half the @chipotle paste{10%g} and all the @mayonnaise{1} into a #small bowl{} and mix together.

== Chicken ==

Heat a glug of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. While the oil heats up, season the @British chicken thighs{2} with salt and pepper. Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken thighs and fry until browned on each side and cooked through, ~{13-15%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken thighs are cooked, remove the pan from the heat and add the lime zest and half the chipotle to the pan, turn the chicken thighs to coat them in the paste. Top them with the grated cheese. Cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #tin foil{} and leave the cheese to melt, ~{3-4%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve the burger buns and pop them into the oven to warm for ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Spread the chipotle mayo on the bottom half of the buns and the guac on the top half. Pop the chicken thighs on a board and carefully chop each of them into 3 or 4 pieces. Share the chicken between in the buns and serve with the wedges and tomato avo salad on the side. Enjoy!